# Counter

A simple counter application built with SwiftUI and SwiftData for iOS.

## Features

- Increment and decrement counter
- Reset counter
- Simple and intuitive UI
- Persistent counter state using SwiftData
- Dark mode support
- Haptic feedback on button presses

## Requirements

- iOS 16.0+
- Xcode 14.0+
- Swift 5.0+
- SwiftUI
- SwiftData

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/nathyanemoreno/counter.git
   cd counter
   ```

2. Open the project in Xcode:

   ```sh
   open Counter.xcodeproj
   ```

3. Build and run the application on your desired simulator or physical device.

## Usage

- Tap the `+` button to increment the counter.
- Tap the `-` button to decrement the counter.
- The counter value is saved automatically using SwiftData.
- The counter value increases/decreases when holding the action buttons
- Order counters manually by the user 

